cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Maisha in your work, please cite it as below."
title: "Maisha (maishac): an agent harness for MISRA C, BARR-C and CERT C compliance"
abstract: >-
  A deterministic orchestration layer (scanning, fingerprinting, persistent
  memory, prioritization, and a verification gate) that sits underneath an LLM
  agent for MISRA C:2012, BARR-C:2018 and CERT C compliance work. It is a
  workflow orchestrator and audit-trail layer, not a qualified/certified
  static-analysis tool, exposed as both a CLI and an MCP server.
type: software
authors:
  - name: "Maisha contributors"
repository-code: "https://github.com/Kiransekar/maisha"
url: "https://github.com/Kiransekar/maisha"
license: MIT
version: "0.3.2"
keywords:
  - misra
  - cert-c
  - barr-c
  - static-analysis
  - mcp
  - agent
  - embedded
  - functional-safety
